Program: Outlook
Title: A Diplomatic Row Between Belarus and Italy
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbslw
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
A couple have caused a diplomatic row between Belarus and Italy over accusations of child abuse and their refusal to return a child to her home. Other items include, Stephen Wagner and his invention using kites to pull ships across the channel; Accusations of corruption amongst the police, including Police Commissioner Heng Pov, in Cambodia; Can money entice high caste Indians to marry low caste partners? Presenter: Frederic Dove. Show less